00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:50,320
And I dare you to comb yours
just once!

263
00:11:50,650 --> 00:11:54,000
I, uh -- I think we should check
off truth or dare and move on.

264
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:56,850
Let's see what our next fun,
fun, fun thing is, shall we?

265
00:11:57,640 --> 00:12:00,460
Hmm, what does this mean?
"Pillow fight"?

266
00:12:00,780 --> 00:12:02,040
Oh, please.

267
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:03,810
I am not at all interested

268
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:06,200
In participating
in something so crude.

269
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:07,190
[ Spits ]

270
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:08,160
Oh!

271
00:12:10,010 --> 00:12:12,330
It...is...on!

272
00:12:13,490 --> 00:12:14,390
Hyah!

273
00:12:15,250 --> 00:12:15,920
[ Thud! ]

274
00:12:17,810 --> 00:12:20,550
[ Whoosh! Whoosh! ]

275
00:12:20,580 --> 00:12:21,900
Yah! Yah! Yah!

276
00:12:23,170 --> 00:12:24,890
[ Whoosh! Whoosh! Whoosh! ]

277
00:12:25,060 --> 00:12:27,480
[ Whiffle! ]

278
00:12:27,540 --> 00:12:29,850
[ Tinkling ]

279
00:12:29,950 --> 00:12:32,180
[ Zip! Zip! Zip! ]

280
00:12:36,460 --> 00:12:37,890
Oh, I get it.

281
00:12:38,490 --> 00:12:40,220
Pillow...fight.

282
00:12:40,410 --> 00:12:41,020
Fun!

283
00:12:41,040 --> 00:12:41,870
Ugh! Aah!

284
00:12:44,330 --> 00:12:45,950
[ Tweet! Tweet! ]
[ Slurring ] uh, girls...

285
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:48,240
maybe we should take it down
a notch.

286
00:12:49,390 --> 00:12:50,600
I will if she will.

287
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:52,530
She started it.

288
00:12:52,650 --> 00:12:53,920
[ Zip! Zip! Zip! ]

289
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:55,320
[ Pop! ]

290
00:12:56,670 --> 00:12:57,910
[ Spitting ]

291
00:12:58,300 --> 00:13:00,960
Maybe we should just call it
a night and get some sleep.

292
00:13:02,710 --> 00:13:07,680
[ Snoring ]

293
00:13:07,900 --> 00:13:10,260
Keep your muddy hooves
on you side of the bed.

294
00:13:10,350 --> 00:13:11,680
My hooves ain't muddy.

295
00:13:12,050 --> 00:13:12,850
They were.

296
00:13:12,990 --> 00:13:14,460
There might still be
a little on them.

297
00:13:14,850 --> 00:13:16,290
There ain't. See?

298
00:13:16,460 --> 00:13:17,550
Ew!

299
00:13:17,740 --> 00:13:18,190
[ Chomp! ]

300
00:13:20,780 --> 00:13:22,310
Now who's bein'
inconsiderate?

301
00:13:22,430 --> 00:13:23,740
[ Grunts ]

302
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:27,660
I have
to make the bed again

303
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:28,960
So the blanket
will be right.

304
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:29,690
Get up.

305
00:13:29,770 --> 00:13:30,520
[ Thud! ]
Hey!

306
00:13:38,930 --> 00:13:40,610
Unh-Unh-Unh.
You'll ruin it.

307
00:13:40,780 --> 00:13:42,300
You have to do it
like this.

308
00:13:43,370 --> 00:13:46,900
[ Grunting ]

309
00:13:47,330 --> 00:13:48,370
[ Sighs ]

310
00:13:49,390 --> 00:13:51,300
Yeah.
That's not gonna happen.

311
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:52,680
Geronimo!

312
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:53,760
[ Sproing! ]
Hey!

313
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:56,310
Ahh.

314
00:13:56,630 --> 00:13:58,350
You did that on purpose.

315
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:00,120
Um, yeah.

316
00:14:00,490 --> 00:14:01,970
Get up
so I can fix it again.

317
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:04,460
Can't hear you.
I'm asleep.

318
00:14:04,560 --> 00:14:07,250
[ Imitating snoring ]

319
00:14:07,370 --> 00:14:08,550
Hmph!

320
00:14:09,650 --> 00:14:11,270
I ain't budgin'.

321
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:14,060
You will
if you want any blanket!

322
00:14:16,920 --> 00:14:17,890
Give it back!

323
00:14:18,250 --> 00:14:19,100
I will not!

324
00:14:19,330 --> 00:14:20,250
Yes, you will!

325
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:22,030
Won't!
Will!

326
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:23,610
Won't!
Will!

327
00:14:23,680 --> 00:14:24,810
Won't!
Will!

328
00:14:24,910 --> 00:14:26,660
Enough!

329
00:14:27,810 --> 00:14:29,750
It says right here
that the number-One thing

330
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:32,270
You're supposed to do
at a slumber party is have fun.

331
00:14:32,540 --> 00:14:35,020
And thanks to you two,
I can't check that off.

332
00:14:35,810 --> 00:14:38,210
I've been tryin' my darndest
to get along.

333
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:41,260
No, it is I
who have been trying my best.

334
00:14:41,470 --> 00:14:42,490
No, it was me.

335
00:14:42,550 --> 00:14:43,390
No, it was I.

336
00:14:43,470 --> 00:14:44,340
Me!
I!

337
00:14:44,730 --> 00:14:47,210
I hope you're happy,
both of you.

338
00:14:47,370 --> 00:14:49,180
You've ruined
my very first slumber party --

339
00:14:49,380 --> 00:14:51,810
The makeover, the s'mores,
truth or dare, the pillow fight!

340
00:14:51,950 --> 00:14:54,800
I mean, is there anything else
that could possibly go wrong?!

341
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:57,510
[ Thunder crashes ]

342
00:14:58,370 --> 00:14:59,560
Sorry I asked.

343
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:04,780
[ Thunder crashes ]

344
00:15:08,620 --> 00:15:09,530
[ All gasp ]

345
00:15:09,610 --> 00:15:12,290
[ Creaking ]

346
00:15:13,390 --> 00:15:14,270
You see?

347
00:15:14,410 --> 00:15:15,960
That's why we needed
to take down

348
00:15:16,010 --> 00:15:19,070
All those loose branches
in town, not spiffy 'em up.

349
00:15:19,490 --> 00:15:20,950
But I --
Out of my way, missy!

350
00:15:21,020 --> 00:15:21,920
Time's a-Wastin'.

351
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:24,720
[ Whirl! Whirl! ]

352
00:15:24,850 --> 00:15:26,230
Wait! Stop! Don't!

353
00:15:26,730 --> 00:15:28,910
No waitin'! No stoppin'!

354
00:15:29,180 --> 00:15:29,860
Doin'!

355
00:15:31,930 --> 00:15:34,960
And that, my friends, is what
we call "gettin' her done."

356
00:15:35,070 --> 00:15:36,290
[ Snap! ]
[ Grunting ]

357
00:15:36,410 --> 00:15:37,620
Aah!
[ Gasps ]

358
00:15:37,690 --> 00:15:40,780
[ Crash! ]

359
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:48,990
[ Rarity whimpering ]

360
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:52,060
I tried to tell you it would
come crashing down in here!

361
00:15:53,670 --> 00:15:55,360
Well, you should have
tried harder!

362
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:58,200
[ Wind whistling ]

363
00:15:58,590 --> 00:16:00,610
[ Rattle! ]

364
00:16:00,860 --> 00:16:03,030
[ Sighs ]
I'm mighty sorry, Twilight.

365
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:06,770
It's --
Well, it's not okay.

366
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,430
There's a giant tree branch
in the middle of my bedroom!

367
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:10,930
And the book
doesn't say anything

368
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:13,210
About having a giant tree branch
at your slumber party --

369
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:15,200
Or at least I haven't found
that entry yet.

370
00:16:15,380 --> 00:16:16,590
[ Whimpers, gasps ]

371
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,910
What in tarnation
are y'all doin' over there?!

372
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:23,460
Cleaning up this mess
somepony made!

373
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:26,320
Who was that again?
Oh, right -- That's you!

374
00:16:29,340 --> 00:16:30,050
[ Zip! ]

375
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,540
We got to do something!

376
00:16:32,990 --> 00:16:34,800
Baking, bffs, brothers.

377
00:16:35,070 --> 00:16:36,820
There's nothing in here
about branches.

378
00:16:38,470 --> 00:16:39,310
[ Boing! Boing! ]

379
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:43,460
[ Grunting ]

380
00:16:44,090 --> 00:16:47,150
Rarity, for pony's sake,
stop sweatin' the small stuff

381
00:16:47,180 --> 00:16:48,670
And help me get rid
of this thing!

382
00:16:48,790 --> 00:16:50,730
[ Wind whistling ]

383
00:16:50,820 --> 00:16:53,360
I said hustle over here
and help me!

384
00:16:56,030 --> 00:16:58,910
Look...i'm sorry,
all right?

385
00:16:59,420 --> 00:17:00,360
What was that?

386
00:17:00,650 --> 00:17:02,380
I said, "i'm sorry"!

387
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:04,050
I should have
listened to you

388
00:17:04,080 --> 00:17:06,210
When you noticed where this here
branch would end up.

389
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:08,510
Your annoyin' attention
to detail

390
00:17:08,540 --> 00:17:10,440
Would have saved us
from this whole mess.

391
00:17:10,650 --> 00:17:13,710
But right now, you need to stop
bein' so dang fussy,

392
00:17:13,810 --> 00:17:15,230
Pickin' up
all those little things,

393
00:17:15,390 --> 00:17:17,210
And help me move
the one big thing in here

394
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:18,530
That actually matters!

395
00:17:20,110 --> 00:17:21,090
Please!

396
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:27,110
Uh, uh,
but I'll get all icky.

397
00:17:27,550 --> 00:17:28,730
Consarn it!

398
00:17:28,860 --> 00:17:31,030
What the -- You --
I mean, yes,

399
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:33,610
Ickiness is often a side effect
of hard work.

400
00:17:33,970 --> 00:17:35,410
But y'all need
to get over it

401
00:17:35,550 --> 00:17:38,630
On account of I just can't
fix this mess I made myself.

402
00:17:39,180 --> 00:17:40,750
I need your help.

403
00:17:45,420 --> 00:17:46,320
Ohh.

404
00:17:46,810 --> 00:17:47,900
Let's do this!

405
00:17:50,790 --> 00:17:53,490
Well, they do have a section
about backyard slumber parties.

406
00:17:53,710 --> 00:17:55,070
Is that what we're doing
right now?

407
00:17:55,180 --> 00:17:56,330
Does this count
as camping?

408
00:17:59,490 --> 00:18:01,250
[ Grunting ]

409
00:18:09,820 --> 00:18:12,120
[ Wind whistling ]

410
00:18:23,530 --> 00:18:25,030
[ Grunts ]

411
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:29,140
[ Gasps ]

412
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:30,190
Ohh.

413
00:18:30,510 --> 00:18:31,610
I look awful.

414
00:18:36,320 --> 00:18:37,050
[ Glop! ]

415
00:18:38,710 --> 00:18:39,380
Better?

416
00:18:42,050 --> 00:18:43,430
[ Chuckles ]
thanks.

417
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:53,810
Ooh, pretty.
Where did these come from?

418
00:18:54,310 --> 00:18:55,610
They're not in the book,
either.

419
00:18:56,240 --> 00:19:01,390
[ Laughter ]

420
00:19:01,690 --> 00:19:03,360
Is it bigger than a barn?

421
00:19:03,820 --> 00:19:05,440
[ Chuckles ]
nope.

422
00:19:05,880 --> 00:19:07,410
Is it smaller
than a saddle?

423
00:19:07,730 --> 00:19:08,770
[ Chuckles ] no.

424
00:19:08,830 --> 00:19:10,860
Only 3 of your 20 questions
left.

425
00:19:11,610 --> 00:19:13,620
We're never gonna guess
what you're thinkin' of.

426
00:19:13,680 --> 00:19:14,530
It could be anything.

427
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,400
Are we getting warmer?

428
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:18,670
Why?
Is it too cold in here for you?

429
00:19:18,730 --> 00:19:19,890
I can turn up the heat.

430
00:19:20,350 --> 00:19:23,110
She means, are we gettin'
any closer with our guesses?

431
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:25,340
Oh! No.

432
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:27,470
And that technically counted
as a question,

433
00:19:27,510 --> 00:19:28,820
So only two more left.

434
00:19:30,310 --> 00:19:31,890
Is it...

435
00:19:32,820 --> 00:19:34,800
a 6-Legged pony
with a purple, polka-Dotted mane

436
00:19:34,820 --> 00:19:36,210
And shootin' stars
comin' out of its eyes...

437
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:37,680
who flies through the air
all over the world

438
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:39,360
To hide magic,
sparkly eggs?

439
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:42,260
That's it!

440
00:19:42,710 --> 00:19:43,900
It is?
It is?

441
00:19:44,280 --> 00:19:46,160
No. [ Chuckles ]

442
00:19:46,630 --> 00:19:47,300
It's that.

443
00:19:49,850 --> 00:19:52,510
But it was just so nice to see
you two finally getting along,

444
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:54,780
I wanted you to be able
to win together.

445
00:19:55,240 --> 00:19:59,030
[ Both laugh ]

446
00:19:59,150 --> 00:20:00,110
See?

447
00:20:00,220 --> 00:20:02,450
We could have been having fun
like this all along.

448
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:06,320
If only somepony
hadn't been so persnickety.

449
00:20:06,850 --> 00:20:08,080
Well, maybe she wouldn't
have been

450
00:20:08,100 --> 00:20:10,210
If somepony else
hadn't been so sloppy.

451
00:20:14,250 --> 00:20:16,400
Sorry for bein'
such a pain in the patootie.

452
00:20:16,750 --> 00:20:18,890
Oh, no.
I'm sure I was much worse.

453
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:21,340
That's kind of you to say,
but I'm the one who's sorry.

454
00:20:21,870 --> 00:20:23,370
Oh, I'm much more sorry
than you are.

455
00:20:23,410 --> 00:20:25,120
[ Scoffs ] are not.
Are too.

456
00:20:25,330 --> 00:20:26,670
Are not.
Are too.

457
00:20:27,010 --> 00:20:28,290
Are not.
Are too.

458
00:20:28,370 --> 00:20:32,000
[ Both laugh ]

459
00:20:32,060 --> 00:20:35,650
I declare my first slumber party
a success.

460
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:37,260
Yeah!
Yeah!

461
00:20:37,280 --> 00:20:38,370
[ Laughs ]

462
00:20:38,590 --> 00:20:40,220
Have fun -- Check.

463
00:20:40,260 --> 00:20:41,610
[ Laughs ]

464
00:20:41,770 --> 00:20:43,650
Rarity: now take two steps
to your left.

465
00:20:44,060 --> 00:20:45,730
Uh, no, my left.

466
00:20:46,030 --> 00:20:48,460
Well, which is it?
Whoa!

467
00:20:49,820 --> 00:20:52,300
That mess is your fault,
not mine.

468
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,770
[ Laughs ]

469
00:20:53,840 --> 00:20:55,650
[ Laughs ]
sorry.

470
00:20:55,690 --> 00:20:58,280
Twilight Sparkle:
"dear princess Celestia,
it's hard to believe

471
00:20:58,310 --> 00:21:00,910
"That two ponies who seem
to have so little in common

472
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:02,430
"Could ever get along.

473
00:21:02,570 --> 00:21:04,270
"But I found out
that if you embrace

474
00:21:04,310 --> 00:21:06,880
"Each other's differences,
you just might be surprised

475
00:21:06,930 --> 00:21:08,960
To discover a way to be friends
after all."

476
00:21:09,370 --> 00:21:10,610
So...

477
00:21:11,970 --> 00:21:14,760
who's up for another
slumber party tomorrow night?

478
00:21:17,050 --> 00:21:18,570
[ Thud! Thud! ]

479
00:21:19,540 --> 00:21:21,420
How about a week from thursday?

480
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:23,380
Ooh, how about two weeks
from saturday?

481
00:21:23,630 --> 00:21:24,800
A month from now?

482
00:21:24,860 --> 00:21:27,750
[ Laughter ]

483
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:30,980
[ Bird chirping ]

